event.title: First Aid/CPR/AED Training
event.description:
Possessing the life saving skills associated with First Aid, CPR and AED use is a valuable skill set for both work environments and home life. Students who attend our course are better equipped to respond to life-threatening situations, when response time is critical. An untrained person responding to a First Aid or CPR situation can cause more harm than good; which is why being properly trained is so important.

Our courses last approximately 6 hours, with a strict limit on participants to ensure ample instructor time and interaction with each student. Our qualified instructors walk students through the theories, laws, and best practices in a lecture and Q & A fashion before delving into the hands-on instruction necessary to demonstrate competence.

Upon completion of the MEDIC First Aid/CPR/AED course, students who pass the written and hands-on exams shall receive a certification in the course.

event.title: Fall Protection Training
event.description: Fall Protection Training is a vital part of keeping employees safe on the job.  Our course provides students with an understanding of fall protection principals, equipment options available for different scenarios, what to look for during inspections, how to properly wear restraint and arrest systems, and discussion on having a rescue plan in place before you start working at height.  Covering both General Industry and Construction standards (29CFR1910 and 29CFR1926), our course prepares your team to stay in compliance and protected when working at height.

event.title: H2S Awareness
event.description: Hydrogen Sulfide (H2S) is an extremely dangerous gas that can be found in serveral industries, including the Oil and Gas Industry.  This course provides the awareness level training needed to understand the dangers of H2S, how to work safely around H2S, and what to do if there is a release.  This course prepares workers to work on sites and in facilities where H2S may be present.  Taught by trained and competent instructors who understand the dangers found in the Energy Industry.

event.title: Medical Evaluation & Fit Testing
event.description: Energes is excited to provide our customers with a respirator fit testing service to ensure employees are prepared to work in a variety of dangerous atmospheres.  Prior to fit testing, individuals must complete a medical questionaire, which is reviewed by a medical professional to ensure each person is medically fit to wear a respirator.  We accomplish this through an electronic questionaire, administered privately and securely, which is reviewed by a medical professional and the results are available within minutes.  Let us help you ensure your employees are fit and ready to work in a variety of dangerous atmospheres.
